I also realized something deeper while doing that.

The Operator Kernel is missing an entire phase.

Right now it mostly describes how to think.

It doesn’t fully describe how cognition regulates itself.

I think the kernel naturally separates into four layers:

PERCEIVE
Observe
Retrieve
↓
EXPLORE
Compare
Translate
Generate
Suspend
Simulate
↓
SELECT
Validate
Distill
Score
Compose
↓
ACT
Build
Archive
Teach
Deploy
Reflect

Notice what changed.

Suspend becomes the gate between exploration and commitment.

That is where wisdom often lives.

